# Physio
--- physio0
Pistols: touch the foot
SideLunges: do it
HandsBehindBackBend: intertwine fingers
SinkArmsInTable: do it
KneelingHipThrusts: do it (eh)
SquatBentSquat: do it
SquattingCalfRaises: do it
SquattingButterfly: pushes
SidePushups: against a table
BellyLyingHipExternalRotation: do it
SquatGroundKneeTouches: do it
HipFlexorStretchLunge: do it
InnerThighLift: leg over other, lift self or leg (eh)
BackLyingHipExternalRotations: combine with clamshells
RH45Throw: throw ball (+ skull crushers)
ProneScorpion: do it
KneeBlockSqueezeBendTouch: do it
WallYogaBlockHipExercise: bend, rotate, back
HipsMotorTangoTwists
--- physio1
RussianCore: v-sit claps, hip against arms, straddle leg lifts, reverse plank leg lifts
WIYT: do it
RotatorCuffOscilations: do it
SidePlankHipup: against a piano chair (very similar to cop twists?)
Clamshells: side-sit into side-plank
LungeExtension: lunge on knee, then extend
SquatBehindReach: do it
SquatTouchSameKnee: do it (eh)
LungeTwists: ok
Bridges: touch, extend, touch | tabletop
BehindHammers: do it
LyingLegRaises: separate or continuous
ArmMotorCrossShoulderTouch: switch upper hand
HipCARs: do it
BandedRotatingHipExtension: do it
TibRaises: with toilet paper roll between
DeepSquatBreath: do it
ShoulderWallRotations: do them
DeadBugs: do it
BirdDog: do it
--- physio2
SidePlank: switch from plank, copenhagen crunches
Butterfly: pull in legs
StandingPancake: press ankle, pull other, sidelunges
SquatingThrorasicReach: do it
NinetyNineties: crossing while on the ground
RecliningHero: do it
LateralRaises: with back-mirror & weighted
LegRaises: in front of a table, leg angle: directly back & 45°
ArmCirclesWeighted: on back, weighted, with leg extensions
TableOppositeCorners: touch opposite table corner, + lift leg
HipStretch: on back, cross leg over, pull other leg into
TurnAnklesLiftLegs: do it
--- physio9
# Hamstring: stretches on each leg (similar to standing pancake), lift opposite
SotsPress: do it, no crouch
ReverseCurls: reverse biceps curls
RotatedKnucklesBehind: rokas aiz muguras, rotēt abos virzienos līdz galam
BroomBehindBack: shoulder form, lift hands
Deadlift: feel the connection in the back, one side is weaker
FakePlanche: do it
BicepsPoses: standing: above head (proper posture + extend), at hips (check symmetry)
Triceps: [arrayRotate(s(`behind the head`), daysModulo(7, 2))]
